    {
      "question": "If two positive integers $a$ and $b$ are written as $a = x^3y^2$ and $b = xy^3$, where $x, y$ are prime numbers, then $LCM(a, b)$ is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The LCM of two numbers is the product of the highest powers of all prime factors involved.",
          "Highest power of $x$ is $x^3$.",
          "Highest power of $y$ is $y^3$."
        ],
        "derivation": "LCM(a, b) = x^{\\max(3,1)} \\times y^{\\max(2,3)} = x^3y^3"
      },
      "topic": "Real Numbers",
      "subtopic": "Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
      "options": [
        "(A) xy",
        "(B) x^2y^2",
        "(C) x^3y^3",
        "(D) x^4y^5"
      ],
