      "question": "The smallest number which is divisible by both $306$ and $657$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The smallest number divisible by both numbers is their LCM.",
          "Given $HCF(306, 657) = 9$.",
          "Using $LCM = \\frac{a \\times b}{HCF}$",
          "LCM = $(306 \\times 657) / 9 = 306 \\times 73 = 22338$"
        ],
        "derivation": "LCM = \\frac{306 \\times 657}{HCF(306, 657)} \\ LCM = \\frac{306 \\times 657}{9} \\ LCM = 34 \\times 657 = 22338"
      },
